<br>
There's enough rules to get on it, but yet there's STILL over 100 people on the thing.  Just because a list exists, does NOT mean it is the end-all, be-all.  I could take a few wizzies, a warrior and a cleric next week, go manaburn his sorry butt after getting aggro and nobody could say otherwise.  Why?  Because that's how it was written, the &quot;waiting list&quot; to me... is stupid.  Especially since whoever is at the bottom of this &quot;list&quot; and follows it now won't even SEE their epic for a good, oh, 18 months!  I've only been PLAYING 18 months.<br>
<br>
This list... is ridiculous.  When Rage was in Naggy's Lair, you basically saw, 3 people... the cleric camping, the next in line and a 'friend of theirs' and that was all the &quot;list&quot; had to it.  Why do people add such stupid politics to a GAME?!  Everytime I look at this so-called &quot;Ragefire List&quot; I crack myself up by all the people actually thinking this is &quot;gospel&quot; and willing to wait 18 months (that's estimating 1 Ragefire per 5 days or so) for a mob that's a free for all, like every other one.  You notice how no other epic has this kind of list, at all?<br>
<br>
Call me weird, but the cleric epic is NOT a required item, NO epic is a required item.  Not everyone has the time to invest nor thinks the returns are that great for the time invested (like most quests).  However, this is not a rant about epic 'quality', it's just this stupid list that everybody seems to think is &quot;gospel&quot; and anyone that goes against it seems to get flamed pretty good, but ready <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In short, Ragefire list is pointless, only makes the bottleneck that was in Naggy's Lair... worse.  The whole 3 clerics there waiting I didn't mind so much... however this list of 103 is ridiculous!  And oddly enough, my cleric is level 8 (oooh), but I haven't touched him in a LONG time (at least 2 months now) due to clerics, in my opinion, being a fairly boring class as it's mostly &quot;heal, sit and med, heal, sit and med&quot; *snore* but that's just my 2cp <p>[58 Troubadour] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33907">Singhawk Stormbringer</a> (Half Elf)
