<br>
The biggest change I can think of as it stands now is, instead of having every cleric on the face of the planet with it, is make a &quot;designated guild cleric&quot; with it, maybe 2 or 3 tops as backups in-case that one is out sick, out of town, etc.  Granted, the cleric epic is nice, but um...<br>
<br>
1) It's a 56 spell, there's enough mana regen opportunities, the &quot;but it's a 96% mana free rez&quot; is not an excuse, you'll just have to *gasp* wait a little longer instead of chain rezzing everybody<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NO</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> epic (including the cleric) is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> required</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to reach certain content.  To be honest, I've seen more people successfully do &quot;whatever&quot; without epics than with them.<br>
