Doing some math...<br>
<br>
We'll say 5 day spawn on Rage (which seems to be the max, not counting &quot;Acts of God&quot;)<br>
103 people on the &quot;list&quot;<br>
That's 515 DAYS until &quot;Person 103&quot; has theirs.<br>
515 days / 30 days (per month, average) - 17.166(repeating) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  months</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> until it's &quot;their turn&quot; - again, not counting server outages, etc<br>
<br>
515 days from July 7th 2002 is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  December 12th 2003 </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> (roughly, give or take a week).  That's an awful long time to be on some &quot;waiting list&quot; just for a game you pay $12.95/mo for - between now and then, you'll be paying an estimated $221.  Also by then, EQ2 will be out, EQOA will be out, MANY other games will be out (Just look at the last 2 weeks - both Neverwinter Nights and Warcraft 3) and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  many many many</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> other games will be out by that time.<br>
