Verant wants every player in the game to die trying to kill their mobs.  Verant makes mobs in this game so powerful that if nobody is attacking it, it will regenerate whatever amount of health is has in seconds.  Verant wants to have large amounts of people to die every time they attempt the high end mobs, and they don't want the people to get back to business fast enough to finish a mob they just wiped on.  Hell, according to the limitations built into the game, you shouldn't ever have the honor to see a cleric with five thousand mana, as that would make the cleric too powerful (/bitchslap verant) <br>
Verant sure as hell doesn't want us to easily overcome obstacles they put in our way.  Getting a raid together with a bunch of clerics with epics would mean almost no downtime.  Imagine a full raid with 15 clerics with epics, hell as soon as a tank falls, another takes his place and like a minute later, dead tank is a rezzed tank and pretty much ready to re-enter the fight, thus helping to enable a raid to finish the job they started.  Verant knows this and they don't want it to be that easy for us to pull off, and so they &quot;limit the influx of cleric epics&quot; into the server, and tada, you got yourself a controversy.  So, while I may have been terse earlier, I'm certainly not being so now, and it is clear to me, the problem is one Verant is not readily willing to change, as the current arrangements fit their liking too much, it will take serverwide action to jar them from their stubbornness.  And also since speaking to verant, whether by email, petition, report has been and most often will be answered with responses defending their side and why things should remain the same, how can the &quot;list&quot; we have adopted on RN exist in even as few as 100 days, let alone 100 individual spawn cycles?  Verant is tacitly telling us &quot;we're not going to help unless the server turns to crap&quot;  so putting 2 and 2 together and arriving at 4, i say the only real path to a solution is what i said in my post above, the entire RN community make ragefire the most disgusting sight in video entertainment.  Talking has proven not to get anywhere, so what else is there to do?  KS'ing and camp stealing has proven to have gotten results, you see RF in skyfire now don't ya?  How did he get there?<br>
Yes this is going to frustrate everyone who has given up hope and got on the list, praying to get RF sometime in this year and a half, rather than never, but the initial frustration might just yield to satisfactory results, too many people are pissed about this.<br>
Jesus Christ, did i just write a damn thesis on this or what?<br>
